      "title": "README",
      "properties": {},
      "widgets_values": [
        "This workflow illustrates how to create and manage style lists,\nenabling rapid switching between preferred styles.\n\nKey considerations:\n\n - Each style list can include up to 10 styles. Multiple lists can be concatenated\n   to increase the number of available styles. In this example, two lists are used,\n   one containing 7 illustration styles and another with 10 photographic styles.\n\n - For each style list, the \"output_to\" parameter must correspond to the selected\n   style in the \"Style & Prompt Encoder\" node. In this case, both lists utilize\n   \"custom 1\" as their \"output_to\" value.\n\n - Typically, all concatenated lists should share the same custom style setting for\n   their \"output_to\" parameter. However, different output_to values can be assigned\n   to each concatenated list if more complex configurations are required"
      ],
      "color": "#432",
      "bgcolor": "#653"
    },
